commit.message:
Restore toJSONFilter instance for pure `a -> [a]`.

This went missing after my ill-considered revision to #105,
commit 183af9d9f1066be974ac55fd23a4c985999d3ce8 .

See jgm/pandoc#8976.

Generalize ToJSONFilter instance.

Previously a pure function `a -> a` could only be promoted to
a filter in IO. Now we allow it to work with any instance of
MonadIO.  (This adds to #105.)
CI: fix cache dir, add ghc 9.6, remove ghc < 8.10.

Remove Null constructor from Block.

[API change]

Closes #91.

ToJSONFilter: Remove unnecessary IO instance.

This is covered already by the MonadIO instance.
Revises #105.

[API change] Add `Figure` block constructor

The new Figure block represents a figure with attributes, caption,
and arbitrary block content.

Co-authored-by: Aner Lucero <4rgento@gmail.com>
Co-authored-by: Christian Despres <christian.j.j.despres@gmail.com>

CI: fix installation of GHC 8.0 and 8.2.

It seems that libtinfo5 is not installed by default, but it's apparently
required for a successful installation of these versions.
CI: add GHC 9.4.4 with cabal 3.8 to test matrix
CI: add caching of dependencies. Closes #102.
CI: Test with latest GHC versions
Improve CI; use ghcup, test with recent ghc versions.
